<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880107-0074 </DOCNO><HL> AFG Buys Ford's Glass Unit </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AFG F </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> IRVINE, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   AFG Industries Inc. said it completed its acquisition of Ford Motor Co.'s Canadian unit, Ford Glass Ltd. for an amount that wasn't disclosed.    Ford Glass makes architectural and commercial flat glass and other non-automotive products. It had estimated 1987 revenue of between 185 million Canadian dollars ($143.4 million) and 190 million dollars.    AFG, a glass producer, had net income of $45.9 million, or $1.81 a share, on sales of $360.3 million for the first nine months of 1987. </TEXT></DOC>